    <item>
      <title>Docs: Docker</title>
      <link>/docs/cloud/devops/docker/</link>
      <pubDate>Sat, 21 Nov 2020 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>/docs/cloud/devops/docker/</guid>
      <description>
        
        
        &lt;br&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;what-is-docker&#34;&gt;What is Docker?&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Docker is an OpenSource containerization platform for &lt;strong&gt;Building, Shipping and Running&lt;/strong&gt; applications using &lt;strong&gt;Container Virtualization technology&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Docker packages all the dependencies in form of a Docker containers to ensure that our applicaton works seamlessly in any of the environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;br&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;docker-image-vs-docker-container&#34;&gt;Docker Image vs Docker Container&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/dotnet/architecture/microservices/container-docker-introduction/media/docker-containers-images-registries/taxonomy-of-docker-terms-and-concepts.png&#34; alt=&#34;Docker Image vs Docker Container&#34;&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;a href=&#34;https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/dotnet/architecture/microservices/container-docker-introduction/media/docker-containers-images-registries/taxonomy-of-docker-terms-and-concepts.png&#34;&gt;Image from microsoft.com&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;br&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;1-docker-images&#34;&gt;1. Docker Images&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Docker uses the concept of Docker images to deploy the Docker Containers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Docker Images can be compaed with a template that can be used to create the Docker Containers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Docker Images are read-only templates.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Docker Images are available on hub.docker.com and can also be created by users.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;br&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;11-how-to-pull-a-docker-image&#34;&gt;1.1 How to pull a Docker image?&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Search an image on DockerHub&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre style=&#34;background-color:#f8f8f8;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#8f5902;font-style:italic&#34;&gt;# docker search IMAGE_NAME &lt;/span&gt;
docker search pytorch
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Pull an image on DockerHub&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre style=&#34;background-color:#f8f8f8;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#8f5902;font-style:italic&#34;&gt;# docker pull IMAGE_NAME &lt;/span&gt;
docker pull pytorch/pytorch
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;12-how-to-check-docker-images&#34;&gt;1.2 How to check docker images?&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;List all the available images on our Docker Engine&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre style=&#34;background-color:#f8f8f8;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;docker images
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;13-how-to-run-a-docker-image&#34;&gt;1.3 How to run a docker image?&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Creates the container and runs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre style=&#34;background-color:#f8f8f8;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;docker run IMAGE_NAME 
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Run specified command&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre style=&#34;background-color:#f8f8f8;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;docker run IMAGE_NAME COMMAND
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Run a container with a specific name&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre style=&#34;background-color:#f8f8f8;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;docker run --name CONTAINER_NAME IMAGE_NAME COMMAND
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Run a container wth an interactive terminal&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre style=&#34;background-color:#f8f8f8;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;docker run -it IMAGE_NAME 
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Run a container in background&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre style=&#34;background-color:#f8f8f8;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;docker run -d IMAGE_NAME COMMAND
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Delete a container as soon as it finishes its execution&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre style=&#34;background-color:#f8f8f8;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;docker run --rm IMAGE_NAME COMMAND
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;14-how-to-remove-a-docker-images&#34;&gt;1.4 How to remove a docker images?&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre style=&#34;background-color:#f8f8f8;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;docker rmi IMAGE_NAME
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;2-containers&#34;&gt;2. Containers&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;21-how-to-check-docker-containers&#34;&gt;2.1 How to check docker containers?&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;List all docker containers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre style=&#34;background-color:#f8f8f8;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;docker ps -a
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;List all running cocker containers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre style=&#34;background-color:#f8f8f8;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;docker ps
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;List only the IDs of cocker containers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre style=&#34;background-color:#f8f8f8;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;docker ps -q
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;22-how-to-start-a-docker-container&#34;&gt;2.2 How to start a docker container?&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre style=&#34;background-color:#f8f8f8;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;docker start CONTAINER_ID
&lt;span style=&#34;color:#8f5902;font-style:italic&#34;&gt;# or &lt;/span&gt;
docker start CONTAINER_NAME
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt; &lt;br&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;23-how-to-exceute-a-child-process-along-the-docker-container-parent-process&#34;&gt;2.3 How to exceute a child process along the docker container parent process?&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre style=&#34;background-color:#f8f8f8;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;docker &lt;span style=&#34;color:#204a87&#34;&gt;exec&lt;/span&gt; CONTAINER COMMAND
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;24-how-to-stop-a-docker-container&#34;&gt;2.4 How to stop a docker container?&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre style=&#34;background-color:#f8f8f8;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;docker stop CONTAINER_ID
&lt;span style=&#34;color:#8f5902;font-style:italic&#34;&gt;# or &lt;/span&gt;
docker stop CONTAINER_NAME
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;br&gt; 
&lt;h3 id=&#34;25-how-to-kill-a-docker-container&#34;&gt;2.5 How to kill a docker container?&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre style=&#34;background-color:#f8f8f8;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;docker &lt;span style=&#34;color:#204a87&#34;&gt;kill&lt;/span&gt; CONTAINER_ID
&lt;span style=&#34;color:#8f5902;font-style:italic&#34;&gt;# or &lt;/span&gt;
docker &lt;span style=&#34;color:#204a87&#34;&gt;kill&lt;/span&gt; CONTAINER_NAME
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt; &lt;br&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;26-how-to-remove-a-docker-container-from-memory&#34;&gt;2.6 How to remove a docker container from memory?&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre style=&#34;background-color:#f8f8f8;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;docker rm CONTAINER_ID
&lt;span style=&#34;color:#8f5902;font-style:italic&#34;&gt;# or &lt;/span&gt;
docker rm CONTAINER_NAME
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt; &lt;br&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;ref&#34;&gt;Ref&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://dev.to/kshitizsaini113/getting-familiar-with-docker-564&#34;&gt;Getting familiar with Docker&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

      </description>
